          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Finding a role as a community hub",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The past few weeks have seen communities, trapped in varous degrees of lockdown, need to organise themselves more than every before. In most places, that's centred around Facebook groups, or WhatsApp chats.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "But one newspaper has made an effort to become the hub for its city:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://www.niemanlab.org/2020/04/how-a-boston-globe-website-started-connecting-those-in-need-because-of-coronavirus-with-those-who-can-help/",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://www.niemanlab.org/2020/04/how-a-boston-globe-website-started-connecting-those-in-need-because-of-coronavirus-with-those-who-can-help/",
          "title": "How a Boston Globe website started connecting those in need because of coronavirus with those who can help",
          "description": "“We love our city and these are our neighbors. It’s a difficult time and if we can make a difference, we will.”",
          "author": "Hanaa’ Tameez",
          "publisher": "Nieman Lab",
          "thumbnail": "https://www.niemanlab.org/images/boston-coronavirus-paramount-theater-ap-700x467.jpg",
          "icon": null
        }
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Now, just imagine they continue to take that community-centric role ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "after",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " the crisis has passed…",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Flickr revamps its groups admin",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Remember Flickr? It was the hot thing in online photo sharing before Instagram came along. Under new owners SmugMug, it's been undergoing something of a renaissance. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "We used to use Flickr as an excellent way of building community around user-generated news photos. Maybe now is the time to revisit that idea?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "bookmark",
        "url": "https://blog.flickr.net/2020/04/01/your-group-admin-experience-just-got-a-whole-lot-better/",
